Def check out @espaciomalcolm and the AfroArgentine org DIAFAR. Tell our hermano Federico we said hi! 👋🏾 October is neighboring Uruguay's official Mes del Tango, Tango Month. Tango was born on the Rio Plata, the area where modern-day, Argentina and Uruguay meet. It was influenced by dances from candombe ceremonies and flourished in the brothels and the marginalized, overcrowded, conventillos of the suburbs of Montevideo and Buenos Aires, where Afrodescendants, immigrants, and gauchos, poor cowboys from the Pampas region who were displaced after the land was given to the elite and white immigrants, were relegated to live. The words “tambo” and “tango” were used to refer to “gatherings of newly arrived Africans to dance to drums,” which colonial powers attempted to ban. The word also referred to the house where Black people carried out their dances.
